@startuml Billing-Sequence-Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 200

title Sistema de Billing y Suscripciones\nDiagramas de Secuencia

' ===============================================
' ACTORS Y PARTICIPANTS
' ===============================================

actor "OrgAdmin" as Admin
participant "Angular\nFrontend" as Frontend
participant "Django\nAPI" as API
participant "Billing\nService" as BillingService
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Stripe\nAPI" as Stripe
participant "Email\nService" as Email
participant "Celery\nWorker" as Celery
participant "Webhook\nHandler" as Webhook

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 1: UPGRADE DE PLAN CON PRORATION
' ===============================================

== 1. Upgrade de Plan (Starter → Professional) ==

Admin -> Frontend: Click "Upgrade to Professional"
activate Frontend

Frontend -> API: GET /api/v1/billing/plans
activate API

API -> DB: SELECT * FROM subscription_plan\nWHERE is_active = true\nORDER BY sort_order
activate DB
DB --> API: [Free, Starter, Professional, Enterprise]
deactivate DB

API --> Frontend: 200 OK {plans: [...]}
deactivate API

Frontend --> Admin: Mostrar comparación de planes
deactivate Frontend

Admin -> Frontend: Confirmar upgrade
activate Frontend

Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/billing/upgrade\n{target_plan: "professional"}
activate API

API -> BillingService: calculate_upgrade(tenant, "professional")
activate BillingService

BillingService -> DB: SELECT * FROM tenant\nWHERE id = ?
activate DB
DB --> BillingService: Tenant\n(current_plan: "starter",\nperiod_end: 2026-02-28)
deactivate DB

BillingService -> DB: SELECT * FROM subscription_plan\nWHERE name = "professional"
activate DB
DB --> BillingService: Plan (price_monthly: 99.00)
deactivate DB

BillingService -> BillingService: calculate_proration()
note right
  **Cálculo de Proration:**
  Días restantes: 19/28
  Starter restante: -$29 * (19/28) = -$19.68
  Pro prorrateado: $99 * (19/28) = $67.18
  Total a cobrar HOY: $47.50
end note

BillingService --> API: {
  current_plan: "starter",
  new_plan: "professional",
  proration_details: {
    starter_refund: -19.68,
    pro_charge: 67.18,
    total_today: 47.50
  },
  next_invoice: 99.00 (2026-02-28)
}
deactivate BillingService

API --> Frontend: 200 OK {upgrade_preview}
deactivate API

Frontend --> Admin: Mostrar desglose:\n"Cargo hoy: $47.50"
deactivate Frontend

Admin -> Frontend: Confirmar pago
activate Frontend

Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/billing/confirm-upgrade\n{plan: "professional"}
activate API

API -> BillingService: process_upgrade(tenant, "professional")
activate BillingService

BillingService -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
activate DB

alt Tenant tiene método de pago
    BillingService -> Stripe: stripe.Charge.create(\n  customer=tenant.stripe_customer_id,\n  amount=4750,\n  description="Upgrade to Professional"
    activate Stripe

    alt Pago exitoso
        Stripe --> BillingService: Charge successful\n(charge_id: ch_xxxxx)
        deactivate Stripe

        BillingService -> DB: UPDATE tenant SET\n  subscription_plan = 'professional',\n  subscription_status = 'active'\nWHERE id = ?
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO invoice\n  (amount: 47.50,\n   status: 'paid',\n   stripe_charge_id: ch_xxxxx)
        DB --> BillingService: Invoice created

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n  (action: 'upgrade_plan',\n   changes: {from: 'starter', to: 'pro'})
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: DELETE FROM redis_cache\n  WHERE key LIKE 'features:{tenant_id}%'
        note right
          Invalidar cache de features
          para desbloquear inmediatamente
        end note

        BillingService -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
        deactivate DB

        BillingService --> API: Upgrade successful
        deactivate BillingService

        API --> Frontend: 200 OK\n{message: "Plan upgraded"}
        deactivate API

        Frontend -> Frontend: Recargar features disponibles

        Frontend --> Admin: ✓ "Upgrade exitoso!\nFeatures Pro desbloqueadas"
        deactivate Frontend

        ' Proceso asíncrono de email
        BillingService -> Celery: send_upgrade_email.delay(\n  tenant_id, invoice_id)
        activate Celery

        Celery -> DB: SELECT tenant, invoice
        activate DB
        DB --> Celery: Data
        deactivate DB

        Celery -> BillingService: generate_invoice_pdf(invoice_id)
        activate BillingService
        BillingService --> Celery: PDF URL (S3)
        deactivate BillingService

        Celery -> Email: send_mail(\n  to: admin@tenant.com,\n  subject: "Upgrade Successful",\n  template: "upgrade_confirmation",\n  attachments: [invoice.pdf])
        activate Email
        Email --> Celery: Email sent
        deactivate Email

        Celery -> DB: INSERT INTO email_log\n  (status: 'sent')
        activate DB
        DB --> Celery: OK
        deactivate DB

        deactivate Celery

    else Pago fallido (tarjeta declinada)
        Stripe --> BillingService: PaymentError\n(card_declined)
        deactivate Stripe

        BillingService -> DB: ROLLBACK TRANSACTION
        activate DB
        deactivate DB

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n  (action: 'upgrade_failed')
        activate DB
        DB --> BillingService: OK
        deactivate DB

        BillingService --> API: Payment failed
        deactivate BillingService

        API --> Frontend: 402 Payment Required\n{error: "card_declined"}
        deactivate API

        Frontend --> Admin: ✗ "Pago rechazado.\nActualizar método de pago."
        deactivate Frontend
    end

else No tiene método de pago
    BillingService --> API: No payment method
    API --> Frontend: 400 Bad Request\n{error: "no_payment_method"}
    Frontend --> Admin: ✗ "Agregar tarjeta primero"
end

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 2: RENOVACIÓN AUTOMÁTICA (CRONJOB)
' ===============================================

newpage Renovación Automática

== 2. Renovación Automática de Suscripciones (Cronjob Diario) ==

Celery -> Celery: Cronjob ejecuta\nprocess_subscription_renewals.delay()\na las 00:00 UTC
activate Celery

Celery -> DB: SELECT * FROM tenant\nWHERE subscription_status = 'active'\nAND subscription_current_period_end = TODAY()
activate DB
DB --> Celery: [Tenant A, Tenant B, ...]
deactivate DB

loop Para cada tenant a renovar
    Celery -> BillingService: renew_subscription(tenant)
    activate BillingService

    BillingService -> DB: SELECT * FROM subscription_plan\nWHERE name = tenant.subscription_plan
    activate DB
    DB --> BillingService: Plan (price_monthly: 99.00)
    deactivate DB

    BillingService -> Stripe: stripe.Charge.create(\n  customer=tenant.stripe_customer_id,\n  amount=9900,\n  description="Subscription renewal - Feb 2026")
    activate Stripe

    alt Pago exitoso
        Stripe --> BillingService: Charge successful\n(charge_id: ch_yyyyy)
        deactivate Stripe

        BillingService -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
        activate DB

        BillingService -> DB: UPDATE tenant SET\n  subscription_current_period_end = TODAY() + 30 days\nWHERE id = ?
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO invoice\n  (amount: 99.00,\n   period_start: 2026-02-01,\n   period_end: 2026-03-01,\n   status: 'paid',\n   stripe_invoice_id: in_xxxxx)
        DB --> BillingService: Invoice created (id: 12345)

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n  (action: 'payment_success')
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
        deactivate DB

        BillingService --> Celery: Renewal successful
        deactivate BillingService

        Celery -> Celery: Encolar email task
        Celery -> Email: send_mail(\n  subject: "Payment Successful",\n  template: "renewal_success",\n  attachments: [invoice.pdf])
        activate Email
        Email --> Celery: Email sent
        deactivate Email

    else Pago fallido
        Stripe --> BillingService: PaymentError\n(insufficient_funds)
        deactivate Stripe

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO invoice\n  (amount: 99.00,\n   status: 'failed')
        activate DB
        DB --> BillingService: Invoice created
        deactivate DB

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n  (action: 'payment_failed')
        activate DB
        DB --> BillingService: OK
        deactivate DB

        BillingService --> Celery: Payment failed (attempt 1)
        deactivate BillingService

        note right of Celery
          **Retry Strategy:**
          - Reintento 1: +3 días
          - Reintento 2: +7 días (total 10 días)
          - Reintento 3: +14 días (total 24 días)
          - Si falla 3 veces: suspender servicio
        end note

        Celery -> Celery: Encolar retry task\nretry_payment.apply_async(\n  args=[tenant_id],\n  countdown=259200  # 3 días
        )

        Celery -> Email: send_mail(\n  subject: "Payment Failed",\n  template: "payment_failed",\n  message: "Update payment method")
        activate Email
        Email --> Celery: Email sent
        deactivate Email

    end
end

Celery -> Celery: Generar reporte de renovaciones
Celery -> DB: INSERT daily_report\n  (successful: 142, failed: 8)
activate DB
DB --> Celery: OK
deactivate DB

deactivate Celery

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 3: REINTENTO DE PAGO FALLIDO
' ===============================================

newpage Reintento de Pago

== 3. Reintento de Pago Fallido (Intento 3 - Último) ==

Celery -> Celery: retry_payment.delay(tenant_id)\n(Día 24 tras fallo inicial)
activate Celery

Celery -> DB: SELECT * FROM tenant\nWHERE id = ?
activate DB
DB --> Celery: Tenant\n(subscription_status: 'past_due')
deactivate DB

Celery -> DB: SELECT * FROM invoice\nWHERE tenant_id = ?\nAND status = 'failed'\nORDER BY created_at DESC\nLIMIT 1
activate DB
DB --> Celery: Last failed invoice
deactivate DB

Celery -> BillingService: retry_charge(tenant, invoice)
activate BillingService

BillingService -> DB: SELECT * FROM payment_method\nWHERE tenant_id = ?\nORDER BY is_default DESC, created_at DESC
activate DB
DB --> BillingService: [Card 1234 (default), Card 5678]
deactivate DB

loop Para cada método de pago
    BillingService -> Stripe: stripe.Charge.create(\n  customer=tenant.stripe_customer_id,\n  source=payment_method_id,\n  amount=9900)
    activate Stripe

    alt Pago exitoso con método alternativo
        Stripe --> BillingService: Charge successful
        deactivate Stripe

        BillingService -> DB: UPDATE tenant SET\n  subscription_status = 'active',\n  subscription_current_period_end = TODAY() + 30 days
        activate DB
        DB --> BillingService: OK
        deactivate DB

        BillingService -> DB: UPDATE invoice SET\n  status = 'paid',\n  paid_at = NOW()
        activate DB
        DB --> BillingService: OK
        deactivate DB

        BillingService --> Celery: Payment recovered
        deactivate BillingService

        Celery -> Email: send_mail(\n  subject: "Payment Successful",\n  message: "Service restored")
        activate Email
        Email --> Celery: OK
        deactivate Email

        Celery --> Celery: ✓ Éxito, terminar loop
        deactivate Celery

    else Pago falla con todos los métodos
        Stripe --> BillingService: PaymentError\n(all methods failed)
        deactivate Stripe

        note right of BillingService
          **Intento 3 fallido = Suspender servicio**
          Tras 3 intentos en 24 días
        end note

        BillingService -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
        activate DB

        BillingService -> DB: UPDATE tenant SET\n  subscription_status = 'suspended',\n  suspended_at = NOW()
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n  (action: 'suspend_tenant',\n   reason: 'payment_failure_3_attempts')
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
        deactivate DB

        BillingService --> Celery: Service suspended
        deactivate BillingService

        Celery -> Email: send_mail(\n  subject: "Service Suspended",\n  template: "suspension_notice",\n  message: "Update payment to restore")
        activate Email
        Email --> Celery: OK
        deactivate Email

        note over Admin
          Admin recibe email crítico
          y debe actualizar pago
          para restaurar servicio
        end note

        deactivate Celery
    end
end

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 4: WEBHOOK DE STRIPE
' ===============================================

newpage Webhook de Stripe

== 4. Webhook de Stripe (invoice.payment_succeeded) ==

Stripe -> Webhook: POST /api/v1/webhooks/stripe\nStripe-Signature: xxx\n{\n  type: "invoice.payment_succeeded",\n  data: {invoice: {...}}\n}
activate Stripe
activate Webhook

Webhook -> Webhook: verify_stripe_signature()\n[stripe.Webhook.construct_event()]

alt Firma válida
    Webhook -> BillingService: handle_webhook_event(event)
    activate BillingService

    alt Event type: invoice.payment_succeeded
        BillingService -> DB: SELECT * FROM tenant\nWHERE stripe_customer_id = ?
        activate DB
        DB --> BillingService: Tenant
        deactivate DB

        BillingService -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
        activate DB

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT OR UPDATE invoice\n  (stripe_invoice_id,\n   status: 'paid',\n   paid_at: NOW())
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: UPDATE tenant SET\n  subscription_status = 'active',\n  subscription_current_period_end = \n    event.data.period_end
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n  (action: 'webhook_invoice_paid')
        DB --> BillingService: OK

        BillingService -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
        deactivate DB

        BillingService --> Webhook: Event processed
        deactivate BillingService

        Webhook --> Stripe: 200 OK\n{received: true}
        deactivate Webhook
        deactivate Stripe

    else Event type: invoice.payment_failed
        BillingService -> DB: UPDATE invoice\n  SET status = 'failed'
        activate DB
        DB --> BillingService: OK
        deactivate DB

        BillingService -> Celery: Encolar retry_payment task
        activate Celery
        deactivate Celery

        BillingService --> Webhook: Event processed
        Webhook --> Stripe: 200 OK

    else Event type: customer.subscription.deleted
        note right
          Usuario canceló suscripción
          desde Stripe dashboard
        end note

        BillingService -> DB: UPDATE tenant SET\n  subscription_status = 'canceled',\n  canceled_at = NOW()
        activate DB
        DB --> BillingService: OK
        deactivate DB

        BillingService -> Email: send_mail(\n  subject: "Subscription Canceled")
        activate Email
        Email --> BillingService: OK
        deactivate Email

        BillingService --> Webhook: Event processed
        Webhook --> Stripe: 200 OK
    end

else Firma inválida (posible ataque)
    Webhook -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n  (action: 'webhook_invalid_signature',\n   ip_address: request.ip)
    activate DB
    DB --> Webhook: OK
    deactivate DB

    Webhook --> Stripe: 401 Unauthorized\n{error: "invalid_signature"}
    deactivate Webhook
    deactivate Stripe
end

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 5: CANCELACIÓN DE SUSCRIPCIÓN
' ===============================================

newpage Cancelación de Suscripción

== 5. Cancelación de Suscripción ==

Admin -> Frontend: Click "Cancel Subscription"
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Frontend: Mostrar modal confirmación:\n"¿Seguro? Acceso hasta 2026-02-28"
Frontend <-- Admin: Confirmar cancelación
Frontend -> Frontend: Solicitar feedback (opcional)
Admin -> Frontend: Razón: "Switching to competitor"

Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/billing/cancel\n{reason: "switching", feedback: "..."}
activate API

API -> BillingService: cancel_subscription(tenant)
activate BillingService

BillingService -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
activate DB

BillingService -> DB: UPDATE tenant SET\n  subscription_status = 'canceled',\n  will_cancel_at = subscription_current_period_end
note right
  **Importante:**
  No cancela inmediatamente.
  Servicio activo hasta fin de período pagado.
end note
DB --> BillingService: OK

BillingService -> Stripe: stripe.Subscription.delete(\n  subscription_id,\n  at_period_end=true)
activate Stripe
Stripe --> BillingService: Subscription scheduled for cancellation
deactivate Stripe

BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n  (action: 'cancel_subscription',\n   metadata: {reason, feedback})
DB --> BillingService: OK

BillingService -> DB: INSERT INTO feedback\n  (tenant_id, type: 'cancellation',\n   reason, feedback)
note right
  Analytics para reducir churn
end note
DB --> BillingService: OK

BillingService -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
deactivate DB

BillingService --> API: Cancellation scheduled
deactivate BillingService

API --> Frontend: 200 OK\n{will_cancel_at: "2026-02-28"}
deactivate API

Frontend --> Admin: ✓ "Suscripción cancelada.\nAcceso hasta 28 Feb 2026."
deactivate Frontend

BillingService -> Email: send_mail(\n  subject: "Subscription Canceled",\n  message: "Access until Feb 28")
activate Email
Email --> Admin: Email confirmación
deactivate Email

note over Celery
  **Cronjob al llegar 2026-02-28:**
  - Migrar tenant a plan Free
  - Deshabilitar features Pro
  - Aplicar límites de plan Free
  - Soft delete datos si configurado
end note

' ===============================================
' NOTAS Y LEYENDAS
' ===============================================

note over Admin, Webhook
  **Business Rules:**
  • Trial: 14 días sin tarjeta requerida
  • Proration: calculado al segundo, no solo días
  • Upgrade: inmediato tras pago
  • Downgrade: efectivo al fin de período
  • Cancelación: acceso hasta fin de período pagado
  • Suspensión: tras 3 intentos fallidos en 24 días
  • Datos: soft delete 30 días tras cancelación
  • Reembolsos: proporcional si se solicita <7 días

  **Webhook Events Escuchados:**
  • invoice.payment_succeeded
  • invoice.payment_failed
  • customer.subscription.deleted
  • customer.subscription.updated
  • payment_method.attached
  • payment_method.detached
end note

legend right
  |= Status |= Significado |
  | trial | Trial activo (14 días) |
  | active | Suscripción activa y pagada |
  | past_due | Pago fallido, en período de gracia |
  | suspended | Servicio suspendido por falta de pago |
  | canceled | Usuario canceló, activo hasta fin período |

  **Stripe Events:**
  • Webhook signature validada con SHA256 HMAC
  • Idempotency key en requests a Stripe
  • Reintentos automáticos si webhook falla (3x)
  • Timeout: 30s para procesamiento de webhooks

  **Email Templates:**
  • upgrade_confirmation.html
  • renewal_success.html
  • payment_failed.html
  • suspension_notice.html
  • cancellation_confirmation.html
endlegend

@enduml
